				<td colspan="2"><span>Cleric is an affective caster/slower (chain stun) into the low 50's when duo'ed with a bard (I've done same level bard/cleric boxed 1-52 also boxed a mediocre equipped 65 bard with a 52 cleric). 
<br />

<br />
Post 50's I aggree with the others, more DPS is/will be handy. Pre-50, I killed as fast as I wanted to with the cleric/bard duo.
<br />

<br />
The versatility of the BL will just be enhanced by a lull puller, cc and extra mana. BL can't snap grab aggo, but with a bard partner it shouldn't matter. Ditto on the necro, more caster and less (ok almost no) melee, but a similar situation, I would think.
<br />

<br />
I would lament the songs not affecting the pet (at least for a long long time), though. Thing is, duo, your best contribution is gonna be doing cc/mana and laying down 3-5 dots/snaring, etc from a safe distance, while your pet aids the bl/necro pet or vise versa.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Edit: Cleric ability to perma stun is limited to lvl 55 mobs, and their nukes while efficient at 49, really fall off compared to other classes after that. I am qualifiying my statement because I have had much less success with the 65 bard/52 cleric combo than with the 52/52 on level appropriate mobs.
<br />

<br />
On the other hand, I have only played BL/Necro to 36 so I only know what I have seen them do at higher levels.
<br />

<br />
Shammy shines with a strong melee, not sure a bard qualifies. But no first hand experience. Their pet appears weaker than other classes, they are behind a bard in melee ability,  so I'm not sure its the best compliment----others will have to say.</span></td>
