			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Good duo class with bard<a name="48080"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 24 04 3:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Over the past few years I have probably responded to posts exactly like this about 100 times.
<br />

<br />
My answer? A mage.
<br />

<br />
Let me first say I can choose from a mage, cleric, or wizard whenever I feel like it for my duo partner but I almost always choose the mage.
<br />

<br />
Why? Well for one thing mages are about the least intensive class in all of EQ to play. This means playing a mage near 100% effeciency will have almost no impact on your bard performance. They are even less intensive than wizard, whom have to concussion to get near 100% effeciency.
<br />

<br />
Secondly they bring excellent DPS, something we sorely lack. Sure a wizard is better burst DPS, but my boxed mage adds around 180-220 DPS without me having to do much of anything except press /pet attack and nuke a few times.
<br />

<br />
Thirdly there are tons of things you can do with the mage/bard combo that would be difficult otherwise. I can solo some very tough mobs with this combo (Took Va'Dynn to 80% while waiting for the rest of the group to arrive with just a bard and mage). Some would say that it is more effective to chant kite a mob that summons and use a cleric to CH you, and for outdoors mobs this is probably true but indoors I would take chained focused Rathe's Son's any day.
<br />

<br />
Fourthly there is an AA that lets bard songs hit pets. What does this mean? That means that with creative exploitation of the enrage behaviour of pets you can do some very interesting things. Like pull 30-50 mobs into your damage shielded pet, watch him go enrage while you twist a 135 point damage shield onto him (with mage DS too) and watch all the low blue mobs eat themselves up on enrage and damageshield. When he dies kite the mobs around on the bard, summon a new pet, suspend/unsuspend to reset the enrage timer (I don't think Sony even knows about this) and rinse and repeat. It is like a faster form of AE kiting without all the risk.
<br />

<br />
Fifthly, Call of the Hero is an incredible pulling aid. Because I am in control of it I can time it to land perfectly to split nearly unsplitable mobs. This relies on a bit of an exploit involving the way mobs chain aggro, but needless to say if you can land CoH a split second after aggro you will get the mob single even if its sitting ontop of 20 of his friends.
<br />

<br />
All in all I just love duoing with my mage. Some people prefer other classes but for my playstyle I love it.</span></td>
